 {"name": "analytics_compare_approaches"}

The comparison of various analytics approaches will be provided in a JSON format, detailing their respective advantages and disadvantages:

```json
[
  {
    "approach": "Batch Analytics",
    "pros": [
      "Processes large amounts of data efficiently.",
      "Provides detailed insights through aggregated results.",
      "Reduces the impact on system performance."
    ],
    "cons": [
      "May have latency due to processing time.",
      "Does not support real-time analysis.",
      "Requires predefined queries and reports."
    ]
  },
  {
    "approach": "Real-Time Analytics",
    "pros": [
      "Provides immediate insights for decision making.",
      "Supports dynamic queries and ad-hoc analysis.",
      "Enables real-time monitoring of key metrics."
    ],
    "cons": [
      "May have higher resource consumption due to continuous processing.",
      "Potential for increased latency during peak usage.",
      "Requires robust infrastructure to handle high volumes of data."
    ]
  },
  {
    "approach": "Streaming Analytics",
    "pros": [
      "Processes data in real-time as it arrives.",
      "Allows for continuous monitoring and analysis.",
      "Can trigger alerts based on predefined conditions."
    ],
    "cons": [
      "Requires specialized infrastructure to handle continuous data streams.",
      "May have higher latency compared to batch analytics.",
      "Complexity in managing real-time data processing."
    ]
  }
]
```

